messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full path
- /api/profiles/{username}/follow

Methods
- all HTTP methods acceptable: false
- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: false
- DELETE: true
- PATCH: false

Explanation
- In main (hello.go) the route group is created as v1 := r.Group("/api") and ProfileRegister is called with v1.Group("/profiles"): users.ProfileRegister(v1.Group("/profiles")). That makes the prefix /api + /profiles.
- In users/routers.go ProfileRegister registers:
  - router.POST("/:username/follow", ProfileFollow)
  - router.DELETE("/:username/follow", ProfileUnfollow)
  which yields the full path /api/profiles/:username/follow. Converting Gin's :param syntax to OpenAPI style gives /api/profiles/{username}/follow.
- Because only POST and DELETE are explicitly registered for that exact path, only POST and DELETE are acceptable. No handlers for GET, PUT, PATCH, HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE or an "ANY" handler are present in the code, so those methods are not acceptable for this path. (There is a GET("/:username") route, but that is for /api/profiles/{username} â€” not for the /follow path.)
